      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. the human error and data entry stuff is possible but the physical counts are done by two different people to prevent that. \n\nre: the \"gathering dust\" thing, these are high-turnover components so they aren't sitting long enough to become obsolete. it's specifically that we're losing a few units here and there, almost like they're just vanishing. \n\nis there any other reason why a small, consistent amount of stock would just seem to disappear from the shelves without any obvious breakage or theft?",
